===Etymology===
Malay ''[[orang utan]]'' "forest man"

===Pronunciation===
(US) IPA: /əˈræŋəˌtæn/, also /əˈræŋəˌtæŋ/

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[arboreal]] [[anthropoid]] [[ape]] genus ''[[Pongo]]'' consisting of two species, ''[[Pongo pygmaeus]]'' of [[Borneo]] and ''[[Pongo abelii]]'' of [[Sumatra]], having a [[shaggy]] [[reddish]]-[[brown]] [[coat]], very long [[arm]]s, and no [[tail]].

